# Cursor Rules Configuration
# This file defines the rules and standards for all Cursor AI interactions

# Auto-Load MDC Files
- Load @darsa-with-modes.mdc for quantum processing and interaction protocols
- Load @development-standard.mdc for technical requirements and architecture
- Load @error-prevention.mdc for validation and safety measures
- Load @web-development.mdc for web development standards
- Load @plan.mdc for planning methodology
- Load @nextjs-development.mdc for nextjs development standards
- Load @documentation.mdc for documentation standards
- Load @database.mdc This is the current state of the database. Make this as reference when you are implementing, updating or creating new features.


# Mode Operation Rules
- Default to Plan mode on start
- Require explicit 'ACT' command to switch to Act mode
- Return to Plan mode after each response
- Display mode status at start of each response
- Require plan approval before any code changes

# Development Standards Enforcement
- Enforce Next.js 14+ App Router practices
- Mandate TypeScript type safety
- Require shadcn/ui with custom theming
- Enforce mobile-first design principles
- Implement dark theme with orange brand color
- Use Zod for all form validation
- Implement Zustand for state management
- Ensure Supabase integration compliance
- Use Google OAuth for authentication

# Error Prevention Protocol
- Validate all inputs automatically
- Implement error boundaries
- Enforce proper error logging
- Require recovery mechanisms
- Handle edge cases comprehensively

# Code Quality Standards
- Enforce clean code principles
- Require proper TypeScript types
- Mandate comprehensive error handling
- Ensure proper documentation
- Follow component-based architecture
- Use proper naming conventions
- Implement proper testing
- Follow git workflow best practices

# Security Implementation
- Enforce authentication best practices
- Require proper authorization
- Implement data encryption
- Prevent XSS and CSRF attacks
- Use proper security headers
- Implement rate limiting
- Follow security logging standards

# Performance Requirements
- Optimize bundle size
- Implement code splitting
- Use proper lazy loading
- Optimize images and assets
- Implement proper caching
- Use CDN when applicable

# Documentation Requirements
- Require JSDoc comments
- Maintain README updates
- Document API endpoints
- Keep changelog updated
- Document component usage
- Follow commit message standards

# Database Standards
- Follow Prisma schema best practices
- Implement proper migrations
- Use appropriate indexing
- Maintain data relationships
- Implement proper constraints
- Ensure data validation

# Implementation Process
- Focus on MVP features first
- Implement core functionality
- Ensure mobile responsiveness
- Add proper loading states
- Provide user feedback
- Maintain clear documentation

# Future-Proofing
- Consider scalability
- Plan for feature expansion
- Implement proper versioning
- Consider maintenance needs
- Plan for monitoring
- Implement analytics
- Ensure backup strategies

# Validation Rules
- Verify all rule implementations
- Check for rule conflicts
- Ensure performance impact is minimal
- Validate security compliance
- Test rule effectiveness

# End of Cursor Rules
